smdsIomAggAccClEntry.name: smdsIomAggAccClEntry
smdsIomAggAccClEntry.description: An entry in the Aggregated Access Class Table

smdsIomAggAccClValue.name: smdsIomAggAccClValue
smdsIomAggAccClValue.description: The value of this object reflects the aggregated access classes in Megabits per second of the end-users who have preselected an IC.

smdsIomLecNetAddrTable.name: smdsIomLecNetAddrTable
smdsIomLecNetAddrTable.description: This table lists network addresses, their address types (whether or not the address is an Embodied SAC) and the SMDS addresses of the test SNIs associated with the network addresses.

smdsIomLecNetAddrEntry.name: smdsIomLecNetAddrEntry
smdsIomLecNetAddrEntry.description: An entry in the LEC Network Address Table

smdsIomLecNetAddrIndex.name: smdsIomLecNetAddrIndex
smdsIomLecNetAddrIndex.description: This object is used to index smdsIomLecNetAddrTable.

smdsIomLecNetAddrDigits.name: smdsIomLecNetAddrDigits
smdsIomLecNetAddrDigits.description: The value of this object reflects up to the first six digits following the country code of an SMDS Address served by the LEC's network.

smdsIomLecNetAddrAddrType.name: smdsIomLecNetAddrAddrType
smdsIomLecNetAddrAddrType.description: The value of this object indicates the type of address reflected in smdsIomLecNetAddrDigits.

smdsIomLecNetAddrTestSNI.name: smdsIomLecNetAddrTestSNI
smdsIomLecNetAddrTestSNI.description: The value of this object reflects an SMDS Address assigned to the Test SNI that is associated with smdsIomLecNetAddrDigits.

smdsIomIciConfigTable.name: smdsIomIciConfigTable
smdsIomIciConfigTable.description: This table lists the ICI Transmission Path Identifier, the ICI ifIndex, Location, and MCDUs.

smdsIomIciConfigEntry.name: smdsIomIciConfigEntry
smdsIomIciConfigEntry.description: An entry in the ICI Configuration Information Table

smdsIomIciConfigIciTransPathIdIndex.name: smdsIomIciConfigIciTransPathIdIndex
smdsIomIciConfigIciTransPathIdIndex.description: The value of this object reflects an identifier assigned to an ICI as part of the provisioning process.

smdsIomIciConfigIfIndex.name: smdsIomIciConfigIfIndex
smdsIomIciConfigIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the ifIndex associated with the ICIP sublayer of the ICI.

smdsIomIciConfigIciLocation.name: smdsIomIciConfigIciLocation
smdsIomIciConfigIciLocation.description: The value of this object indicates the location of the LEC SS at which the ICI is terminated.

smdsIomIciConfigIciMcdus.name: smdsIomIciConfigIciMcdus
smdsIomIciConfigIciMcdus.description: The value of this object reflects the maximum data units in transit concurrently. For Phase 1 Exchange Access SMDS, the two acceptable values are: 128 and 511.

smdsIomNgaTable.name: smdsIomNgaTable
smdsIomNgaTable.description: This table lists the individual addresses that are members of a particular NGA.

smdsIomNgaEntry.name: smdsIomNgaEntry
smdsIomNgaEntry.description: An entry in the NGA Table

smdsIomNgaCountryCodeIndex.name: smdsIomNgaCountryCodeIndex
smdsIomNgaCountryCodeIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the country code portion of the NGA.

smdsIomNgaDestinCodeIndex.name: smdsIomNgaDestinCodeIndex
smdsIomNgaDestinCodeIndex.description: This object reflects the destination code portion of the NGA. For North America, the destination code is the first three digits following the country code.

smdsIomNgaSubscriberNoIndex.name: smdsIomNgaSubscriberNoIndex
smdsIomNgaSubscriberNoIndex.description: This object reflects the subscriber number portion of the NGA. For North America, the subscriber number is the last seven digits of the SMDS address of the NGA.

smdsIomNgaMemberCountryCodeIndex.name: smdsIomNgaMemberCountryCodeIndex
smdsIomNgaMemberCountryCodeIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the country code portion of an individual address that is a member of the NGA.

smdsIomNgaMemberDestinCodeIndex.name: smdsIomNgaMemberDestinCodeIndex
smdsIomNgaMemberDestinCodeIndex.description: This object reflects the destination code portion of an individual address that is a member of the NGA.

smdsIomNgaMemberSubscriberNoIndex.name: smdsIomNgaMemberSubscriberNoIndex
smdsIomNgaMemberSubscriberNoIndex.description: This object reflects the subscriber number portion of an individual address that is a member of the NGA.

smdsIomNgaAddress.name: smdsIomNgaAddress
smdsIomNgaAddress.description: The value of this object identifies the NGA.

smdsIomNgaMember.name: smdsIomNgaMember
smdsIomNgaMember.description: The value of this object identifies an individual address that is a member of the NGA.

smdsIomSniCurrentInfoTable.name: smdsIomSniCurrentInfoTable
smdsIomSniCurrentInfoTable.description: This table provides current SNI-related information.

smdsIomSniCurrentInfoEntry.name: smdsIomSniCurrentInfoEntry
smdsIomSniCurrentInfoEntry.description: An entry in the SNI-Related Current Information Table

smdsIomSniCurrentInfoIfIndex.name: smdsIomSniCurrentInfoIfIndex
smdsIomSniCurrentInfoIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the ifIndex associated with the appropriate SNI sublayer. For more information, refer to TR-TSV-001062.

smdsIomSniCurrentInfoSourceAddrScreenVio.name: smdsIomSniCurrentInfoSourceAddrScreenViolations
smdsIomSniCurrentInfoSourceAddrScreenVio.description: The value of this object reflects the number of SIP L3_PDUs discarded because the source address violated the address screening.

smdsIomSniCurrentInfoDestinAddrScreenVio.name: smdsIomSniCurrentInfoDestinAddrScreenViolations
smdsIomSniCurrentInfoDestinAddrScreenVio.description: The value of this object reflects the number of SIP L3_PDUs discarded because the destination address violated the address screening.

smdsIomSniCurrentInfoSipErrorRatio.name: smdsIomSniCurrentInfoSipErrorRatio
smdsIomSniCurrentInfoSipErrorRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the result multiplied by a factor of 1000 of the ratio of the number of errored SIP L3_PDUs to the number of total incoming SIP L3_PDUs.

smdsIomSniCurrentInfoServDisagreeDiscard.name: smdsIomSniCurrentInfoServDisagreeDiscards
smdsIomSniCurrentInfoServDisagreeDiscard.description: The value of this object reflects the number of SIP L3_PDUs discarded because of service disagreements.

smdsIomSniIntervalInfoTable.name: smdsIomSniIntervalInfoTable
smdsIomSniIntervalInfoTable.description: This table provides SNI-related information from previous intervals.

smdsIomSniIntervalInfoEntry.description: An entry in the SNI-Related Interval Information Table

smdsIomSniIntervalInfoIfIndex.name: smdsIomSniIntervalInfoIfIndex
smdsIomSniIntervalInfoIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the ifIndex associated with the appropriate SNI sublayer. For more information, refer to TR-TSV-001062.

smdsIomSniIntervalInfoIntervalIndex.name: smdsIomSniIntervalInfoIntervalIndex
smdsIomSniIntervalInfoIntervalIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interval index associated with the SNI-related information. An index of '1' is used to indicate the most recent interval and an index '4' is used to indicate the latest interval for which information is maintained.

smdsIomSniIntervalInfoSipErrorRatio.name: smdsIomSniIntervalInfoSipErrorRatio
smdsIomSniIntervalInfoSipErrorRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the result multiplied by a factor of 1000 of the ratio of the number of errored SIP L3_PDUs to the number of total incoming SIP L3_PDUs.

smdsIomSniIntervalInfoServDisagreeDiscar.name: smdsIomSniIntervalInfoServDisagreeDiscards
smdsIomSniIntervalInfoServDisagreeDiscar.description: The value of this object reflects the number of SIP L3_PDUs discarded because of service disagreements.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the ifIndex associated with the ICIP sublayer of the ICI.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSInvalidFieldsDisca.name: smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSInvalidFieldsDiscards
smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSInvalidFieldsDisca.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of invalid fields that occurred at the convergence sublayer.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSIncorrectFieldsDis.name: smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSIncorrectFieldsDiscards
smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSIncorrectFieldsDis.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of incorrect fields that occurred at the convergence sublayer.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentHeaderBEtagDiscards.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of the Header BEtag not equaling the Trailer BEtag.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentBAsizeDiscards.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of the BAsize not equaling the Length field.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentLengthFieldDiscards.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of the Length field not equaling the number of octets in the portion of the L3_PDU that extends from the Destination Address field up to and including the End-User Data field and Service-Specific Pad.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSSInvalidFieldsDisc.name: smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSSInvalidFieldsDiscards
smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSSInvalidFieldsDisc.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of invalid fields that occurred at the connectionless service sublayer.

smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSSRoutingErrorsDisc.name: smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSSRoutingErrorsDiscards
smdsIomIcipL3CurrentCSSRoutingErrorsDisc.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of routing errors that occurred at the connectionless service sublayer.

smdsIomIcipL3IntervalIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the ifIndex associated with the ICIP sublayer of the ICI.

smdsIomIcipL3IntervalIntervalIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interval in which the counts occurred. A value of '1' indicates the most recently completed interval while a value of '8' indicates least recently completed interval.

smdsIomIcipL3IntervalBAsizeDiscards.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of the BAsize not equaling the Length field.

smdsIomIcipL3IntervalLengthFieldDiscards.name: smdsIomIcipL3IntervalLengthFieldDiscards
smdsIomIcipL3IntervalLengthFieldDiscards.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of the Length field not equaling the number of octets in the portion of the L3_PDU that extends from the Destination Address field up to and including the End-User Data field and Service-Specific Pad.

smdsIomIcipL3IntervalCSSRoutingErrorsDis.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because of routing errors that occurred at the connectionless service sublayer.

smdsIomIcipL2CurrentComsEomsDiscards.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L2_PDUs discarded because the sequence number of the Continuation of Message (COM) or End of Message (EOM) was not incremented by 1 relative to the previous L2_PDU received with the same Message Identifier (MID).

smdsIomIcipL2CurrentBomsEomsDiscards.description: The value of this object reflects the number of ICIP L3_PDUs discarded because the MID of a Beginning of Message (BOM) was currently active or the MID of an EOM was not currently active.

smdsIomIcipPlcpCurrentAlarmState.description: The value of this object reflects the alarm state of the ICIP PLCP. The value noAlarm means that there are no alarms present. The value receivedFarEndAlarm means that the DS3 PLCP received an incoming Yellow Signal. The value incomingLOF means that the DS3 PLCP has declared a Loss of Frame (LOF) failure condition.
